(42, 11, 34, 19, 119, 18, 18, 'thine eye is single', 'Connection of Light and Eyes', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of the eyes in perceiving truth and understanding. In Luke, a ''single'' eye brings light, while in Psalms, an ''open'' eye seeks to behold wondrous things.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 34, 24, 5, 21, 21, NULL, 'Connection of Sight and Understanding', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of sight and understanding. Luke discusses the eye''s role in perceiving light, while Jeremiah critiques those who have eyes but do not see, highlighting a lack of spiritual insight.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 34, 45, 11, 8, 10, NULL, 'Connection of Spiritual Perception', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of sight and perception. Luke discusses the condition of the eye affecting the body''s light or darkness, while Romans references eyes that are darkened, preventing perception. This connection highlights the spiritual blindness and its consequences.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 34, 47, 4, 4, 4, 'light of the body is the eye', 'Connection of Light and Darkness', 'This connection highlights the theme of light and darkness in both passages. Luke discusses the eye as a source of light or darkness in the body, while 2 Corinthians mentions the blinding of minds, preventing the light of the gospel from shining.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 34, 51, 3, 22, 22, 'thy whole body also is full of light', 'Connection of Singleness of Heart', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of having a focused and sincere intention. In Luke, a ''single'' eye leads to a body full of light, while in Colossians, ''singleness of heart'' is encouraged in serving. This connection highlights the theme of inner purity and sincerity in one''s actions.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 35, 20, 16, 25, 25, 'light which is in thee', 'Light and Rightness Connection', 'This connection highlights the importance of discernment in one''s inner life. Both passages emphasize that what seems right or illuminating may lead to darkness or death if not carefully evaluated.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 35, 61, 1, 9, 9, 'the light which is in thee', 'Connection of Spiritual Blindness', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of spiritual awareness. Luke warns against the danger of darkness within, while 2 Peter describes the consequences of spiritual blindness and forgetting one''s purification from sin.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 35, 59, 3, 13, 17, 'the light which is in thee', 'Wisdom and Inner Light', 'This connection highlights the importance of inner wisdom and the nature of one''s heart. Luke warns against darkness within, while James contrasts earthly wisdom with the purity of wisdom from above.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 35, 46, 1, 19, 21, 'light which is in thee', 'Wisdom and Light Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between divine wisdom and human understanding. Luke warns against the darkness within, while 1 Corinthians highlights how worldly wisdom fails to recognize God, suggesting that true understanding comes from divine revelation.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 35, 23, 5, 20, 21, 'light which is in thee', 'Light and Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between light and darkness, warning against the misinterpretation of moral truths. Luke''s admonition to ensure one''s light is not darkness parallels Isaiah''s condemnation of those who confuse good and evil.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 35, 43, 9, 39, 41, 'the light which is in thee', 'Connection of Light and Blindness', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of light and darkness, with Luke warning against the darkness within and John discussing spiritual blindness. This connection highlights the theme of perception and understanding in relation to spiritual truth.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 35, 45, 1, 22, 22, 'light which is in thee', 'Wisdom and Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between light and darkness, suggesting that those who believe they possess wisdom may actually be in darkness. This connection highlights the folly of relying on one''s own understanding instead of true light.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 36, 20, 20, 27, 27, 'the bright shining of a candle', 'Light and the Spirit', 'This connection highlights the concept of light as a source of understanding and guidance. Both passages emphasize the role of light in revealing the inner workings of a person, with the spirit being likened to a candle that illuminates the depths of one''s being.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 36, 20, 4, 18, 19, 'full of light', 'Light and Darkness Contrast', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between light and darkness. Luke 11:36 speaks of a body full of light, while Proverbs 4:18-19 describes the path of the just as a shining light and the way of the wicked as darkness.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 36, 47, 4, 6, 6, 'full of light', 'Light and Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of light overcoming darkness. Luke speaks of the body being full of light, while 2 Corinthians highlights God commanding light to shine out of darkness, suggesting a transformative illumination.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 36, 55, 3, 15, 17, 'full of light', 'Connection of Light and Scripture', 'This connection highlights the theme of illumination, where Luke speaks of the body being full of light, paralleling the idea in 2 Timothy that scripture provides wisdom and guidance. Both passages emphasize the transformative power of light and knowledge in leading to righteousness and good works.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 36, 61, 3, 18, 18, 'full of light', 'Growth in Spiritual Light', 'This connection highlights the theme of spiritual illumination and growth. Luke emphasizes being full of light, while 2 Peter encourages growth in knowledge, suggesting a progression towards greater understanding and enlightenment.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 36, 19, 119, 97, 105, 'full of light', 'Light and Understanding Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of light as a source of understanding and guidance. Both passages emphasize that being filled with light leads to wisdom and clarity in one''s path.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 36, 51, 3, 16, 16, 'full of light', 'Light and Wisdom Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of illumination and understanding. Both passages emphasize the importance of being filled with light and wisdom, suggesting that a life enriched by the word of Christ brings clarity and guidance.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 37, 42, 7, 36, 36, NULL, 'Pharisees Inviting Jesus', 'This connection highlights the repeated action of a Pharisee inviting Jesus to dine with him. Both passages emphasize the hospitality extended to Jesus by a Pharisee, showcasing similar social interactions.', 'parallel', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 37, 46, 9, 19, 23, 'dine with him', 'Dining and Relational Engagement', 'This connection highlights the theme of relational engagement in both passages. In Luke 11:37, Jesus dines with a Pharisee, demonstrating his willingness to connect with others, while in 1 Corinthians 9:19-23, Paul expresses his adaptability to different groups to gain them for the gospel.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 37, 42, 14, 1, 1, 'dine with him', 'Dining with Pharisees', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus dining with Pharisees, highlighting social interactions and scrutiny. The act of eating in these contexts serves as a backdrop for discussions on law and behavior.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 38, 40, 15, 2, 3, 'not first washed before dinner', 'Washing Before Eating', 'This connection highlights the emphasis on washing before meals in both passages. In Luke, the Pharisee marvels at the lack of washing, while in Matthew, the disciples are criticized for not following the tradition of washing hands.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 38, 41, 7, 2, 5, 'washed before dinner', 'Connection of Ritual Cleanliness', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of washing before eating, highlighting the Pharisees'' focus on ritual cleanliness. The marveling of the Pharisee in Luke reflects the criticism found in Mark regarding unwashen hands.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 38, 43, 3, 25, 25, 'washed before dinner', 'Connection of Purification Practices', 'This connection highlights the theme of purification rituals in both passages. In Luke, the Pharisee''s concern about washing before dinner reflects Jewish customs, while in John, the discussion among John''s disciples and the Jews centers on purifying practices.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 39, 1, 6, 5, 5, 'full of ravening and wickedness', 'Connection of Wickedness in Hearts', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of wickedness within. Luke highlights the Pharisees'' inward corruption, while Genesis describes the pervasive evil in human hearts.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 39, 20, 30, 12, 12, NULL, 'Purity and Inner Filth', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between outward appearances and inner moral condition. Luke highlights the Pharisees'' focus on external cleanliness, while Proverbs points to a generation that is ''pure in their own eyes'' despite their inner filthiness.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 39, 56, 1, 15, 15, NULL, 'Purity and Defilement Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between outward appearances and inner purity. Luke highlights the Pharisees'' focus on external cleanliness, while Titus discusses the defilement of the mind and conscience.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 39, 40, 7, 15, 15, 'inward part is full of ravening', 'Inward vs. Outward Cleanliness', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between outward appearances and inward reality. Luke highlights the Pharisees'' focus on external cleanliness while their hearts are corrupt, paralleling Matthew''s warning about false prophets who appear innocent but are actually dangerous.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 39, 40, 15, 19, 19, 'your inward part is full of ravening', 'Connection of Inner and Outer Purity', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between outward appearances and inner moral condition. Luke highlights the Pharisees'' focus on external cleanliness, while Matthew identifies the evil thoughts that arise from the heart.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
